{"title":"Eight-Week Knee-Conscious Powerbuilding Cut","weeks":8,"progression":[{"applies":"Competition squat, bench press, and deadlift","rule":"Weeks 1 and 5 use top sets at RPE 7.5-8; weeks 2 and 6 use RPE 8; weeks 3 and 7 use RPE 8-8.5. Perform the listed back-offs from that day's top set. When all prescribed reps are completed with stable technique and the top set stays at or below the target RPE, add 2.5 kg to bench or 5 kg to squat/deadlift in the next build wave. Never increase load through knee pain."},{"applies":"Secondary compound lifts and weighted pull-ups","rule":"Use double progression within the listed rep range. Add reps until every set reaches the top of the range at 1-2 RIR, then add 2.5-5% load and return to the bottom of the range."},{"applies":"Arm, delt, calf, leg-curl, and hip-abduction accessories","rule":"Use double progression. When every set reaches the top of the rep range at 0-1 RIR with controlled technique, increase load by the smallest available increment and reset to the bottom of the range."},{"applies":"Explosive drills, loaded carries, and zone-2 cardio","rule":"For explosive drills, add no fatigue-driven reps; stop when speed or landing quality declines. For carries, add 2-5% load after all four trips are completed without grip or posture breakdown. For cardio, build from 12 to 15 minutes before increasing incline or speed."}],"days":[{"day":1,"title":"Upper Strength and Back Width","sections":[{"name":"Warmup","type":"warmup","groups":[{"type":"single","exercises":[{"name":"Upper-body preparation circuit","sets":1,"reps":"8-10 minutes","notes":"2 rounds: 12 band pull-aparts, 10 scapular push-ups, 8 light cable rows, then unlogged bench ramp-up sets.","countsTowardVolume":false,"tags":{"primary":[],"secondary":[],"incidental":[],"modifiers":["warmup"]}}]}]},{"name":"Primary Strength","type":"strength","groups":[{"type":"single","exercises":[{"name":"Competition bench press","sets":4,"reps":"1 top set x 3; 3 back-off sets x 5","l